Testing_Period: The specific time period during which the software quality assurance testing is being analyzed. This relates to when the testing efforts are being evaluated.
UX_UI_Testing_Allocation: The proportion of testing time dedicated to user experience and interface issues. This metric helps in understanding the focus on enhancing user interactions with the software.
Total_Testing_Hours: The total number of hours allocated for software quality assurance testing in the given period. This provides context for the proportion of time spent on specific issues.
EV_Model_Focus: The specific electric vehicle model or models that are the focus of the testing efforts. This helps in associating testing allocation with particular products.
QA_Engineer_Responsible: The name of the Quality Assurance Engineer responsible for overseeing the testing allocation. This relates to accountability and traceability in testing processes.
